==English==

===Verb form===
'''boiling'''

# Present participle of '''to [[boil]]'''.

===Noun===
'''boiling''' (''[[uncountable]]'')
#The process of [[change|changing]] the [[state]] of a [[substance]] from [[liquid]] to [[gas]] by [[heat]]ing it past its [[boiling point]].
[[Category:English nouns]]

====Translations====
*French: [[ébullition]] ''f''

===Adjective===
'''boiling''' (''not comparable'')

#That boils or boil.
#:''boiling kettle''
#:''boiling oil''
#(''of a thing; informal'') Extremely hot.
#:''The radiator is boiling &ndash; I'm going to turn it down a bit.''
#(''of a person; informal'') Feeling uncomfortably hot.
#:''I'm boiling &ndash; can't we open a window?''
#(''of the weather'') Very hot.
#:''It's boiling out today!''

